sql:
SELECT SUM(amount) AS total_adjustments
FROM net_income_adjustments
WHERE period_id = 0;

SELECT period_id, SUM(amount) AS total_depreciation
FROM depreciation_details
GROUP BY period_id;

SELECT description, amount, department_id, region_id, created_at
FROM net_income_adjustments
WHERE period_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
Adjusted net income refers to the net income after considering various adjustments such as depreciation, operating cash flows, and changes in accounts receivables, providing a more accurate picture of a company's financial health; 

Depreciation represents the decrease in the value of assets over time, typically due to wear and tear; 

Operating cash flows represent the cash inflows and outflows from a company's core business operations;

Accounts receivables refer to the amount of money customers owe to a business for goods or services sold on credit.
